# Automatic Street Light using LDR and Arduino

This project demonstrates an **Automatic Street Light System** using an **LDR sensor** (Light Dependent Resistor). The system automatically switches **street lights ON** in the absence of sunlight (darkness) and switches them **OFF** when there is sufficient daylight, thereby saving energy.

---

## ðŸ“Œ Components Used
- Arduino UNO (or any compatible board)  
- LDR Sensor  
- 10kÎ© Resistor  
- LED (as street light)  
- Jumper wires  
- Breadboard / PCB  

---

## âš¡ Working Principle
- The **LDR sensor** detects the ambient light intensity.  
- When light intensity is **low (night)** â†’ Arduino turns **LED ON** (street light ON).  
- When light intensity is **high (day)** â†’ Arduino turns **LED OFF** (street light OFF).  

This makes the system fully automatic and efficient.

